Description: Fragment of neck and sub-round handle to sharp turn of Rhodian pottery transport amphora. Rectangular stamp. Clay fine light buff-brown.
Curator's comments: Name Euanor. From the same die as Alexandria, Greco-Roman Museum, ABC 0122.04 and BM 1987,1110.115. Trimmed.
Bibliographic references: Villing et al 2013-2015 / Naukratis: Greeks in Egypt (JB.1154)
